I've been working on a whole approach/methodology/system about the =
agile/adaptive organization (I prefer adaptive, but may succumb to the =
halo value of the word agile) - that Agile was a response to structural =
limitations in software development and now the world is being eaten by =
software, so it's superstructures become a higher order framework for =
how to do business in a software-driven world. Happy to share thoughts =
on this specifically for the talking points, but would love to find a =
way to get a bit of credit for it, either as part of, or separate from =
the stuff above.

